<example id="fs-id1170653836983"><exercise id="fs-id1170653768882">
<problem id="fs-id1170653768884">
<para id="fs-id1170653769448">**Soleil was on a road trip and saw a sign that said the next rest stop was in 100 kilometers. How many miles until the next rest stop (rounded to the nearest mile)? </para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1170652658229">
<title>Solution</title>
<table id="eip-310" summary=".">
<tgroup cols="2"><tbody>
  <row>
    <entry/>
    <entry><m:math><m:mtext>100 kilometers</m:mtext></m:math></entry>
  </row>
    <row>
    <entry>Multiply by a unit conversion factor relating km and mi.</entry>
    <entry><m:math><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>kilometers</m:mtext><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>mile</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1.61</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>kilometer</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:math></entry>
  </row>
    <row>
    <entry>Simplify.</entry>
    <entry><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mtext>100 miles</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1.61</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:math></entry>
  </row>
    <row>
    <entry>Divide.</entry>
    <entry><m:math><m:mtext>62 miles.</m:mtext></m:math></entry>
  </row> 
  <row>
    <entry/>
    <entry>Soleil will travel 62 miles.</entry>
  </row>
</tbody>


</tgroup>
</table></solution>
</exercise>
