<section id="fs-id1170653735611" class="everyday">
<title>Everyday Math</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1170653768062">
<problem id="fs-id1170653768064">
<para id="fs-id1170654115069"><emphasis effect="bold">Nutrition</emphasis> Julian drinks one can of soda every day. Each can of soda contains 40 grams of sugar. How many kilograms of sugar does Julian get from soda in 1 year?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1170652624003">
<para id="fs-id1170654158608">14.6 kilograms</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1170654233918">
<problem id="fs-id1170654233920">
<para id="fs-id1170654021916"><emphasis effect="bold">Reflectors</emphasis> The reflectors in each lane-marking stripe on a highway are spaced 16 yards apart. How many reflectors are needed for a one mile long lane-marking stripe?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
</section>
<section id="fs-id1170653879428" class="writing">
<title>Writing Exercises</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1170653885012">
<problem id="fs-id1170653885014">
<para id="fs-id1170654143671">Some people think that <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>65</m:mn><m:mtext>°</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>to</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mn>75</m:mn><m:mtext>°</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> Fahrenheit is the ideal temperature range.</para>
<list id="fs-id1166422561017" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="circled">
<item><span class="token">ⓐ</span> What is your ideal temperature range? Why do you think so?</item>
<item><span class="token">ⓑ</span> Convert your ideal temperatures from Fahrenheit to Celsius.</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1167268234022">
<para id="fs-id1167268234024">Answers may vary.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1170654230664">
<problem id="fs-id1170653769542">
<list id="fs-id1166422865348" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="circled">
